PAPERLESS PUBLISHING AND POTENTIAL INSTITUTIONAL CHANGE.
     
ADAPTED FROM A PAPER PRESENTED AT THE 5TH ANNUAL SPRING CONFERENCE OF THE
LIBRARIANS' ASSOCIATION, UNIVERSITY OF NORTH CAROLINA, CHAPEL HILL, 9 MAR 81.
EXISTING TECHNOLOGIES RAISE THE PROBABILITY OF WALL-LESS 'ELECTRONIC
LIBRARIES' IN THE FUTURE. LIBRARIANS AND PUBLISHERS ALIKE SHOULD BE PREPARED
FOR INSTITUTIONAL REORGANISATION AS 'PAPERLESS PUBLISHING' TAKES HOLD.
